HEADWORD: Emacerate
<hw>E*mac"er*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>emaceratus</ets> emaciated; <ets>e</ets> + <ets>macerare</ets> to
make soft.]</ety> <def>To make lean or to become lean; to
emaciate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bullokar.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
